What is YAML?

Overview of YAML data serialization language and its benefits.

Building a deep understanding of YAML's syntax and its supported data types.

Generating powerful structures using nested containers

Creating YAML files for storing and exchanging data.

Working with anchors in documents

Learning the purpose of YAML and its usage in various tools and applications.

Course Overview

In this course, you will run through a comprehensive overview of the YAML data serialization language and its syntax. You will also cover the basic concepts behind this language, understand its main features, and the capabilities of YAML. You will kick things off by understanding what exactly YAML is. You will then move on to more concrete topics like syntax, data types, and more complex data types such as sequences, mappings, and pairs. By the end of this course, you will have a great new skill that is transferable and highly applicable.
